#
# BedrockOnLinux — Run Minecraft Bedrock (Windows GDK build) on any Linux,
# multiplayer included, with everything bundled. No 40 apps to install.
#
# SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
# Project: https://github.com/BedrockOnLinux/BedrockOnLinux  (placeholder)
#
# What it does, fully automatically, in ONE binary:
#   * downloads GDK-Proton (Weather-OS) and binary-patches it so Minecraft
#     Bedrock GDK actually launches under Wine (combase.RoOriginateErrorW +
#     ntdll stub_entry_point — the two fixes that make it work);
#   * downloads umu-launcher (Steam Linux Runtime) so it runs on every distro;
#   * downloads a bundled Java 25 + the ProxyPass build matching YOUR Minecraft
#     version, and runs it in the background so multiplayer works (WineGDK has
#     no in-game Microsoft login; ProxyPass authenticates outside Wine);
#   * sets up the Wine prefix, SSL/curl, GameInput, options.txt;
#   * launches the game.
#
# It NEVER downloads Minecraft itself. You must provide your own legally
# obtained Bedrock GDK files (extracted from your Windows/Xbox install).
#
# Host requirements (present on virtually every Linux): python3, tar,
# curl OR wget, and bubblewrap (`bwrap`). Run `bedrock-on-linux doctor`.

